The code is to count the number of nodes which are stronger than each team in a directed graph. The number of stronger nodes is the degree of each team. The team that has the degree 0 is the champion if there is only one team with degree 0. If there are more than one team with degree 0, return -1 because there is no unique champion. The missing code in the above code is to increase the degree of each team that is stronger than another team.

Here is the completed code:

```java
class Solution {
    public int findChampion(int n, int[][] edges) {
        int[] degree = new int[n];
        for (int[] e : edges) {
            degree[e[1]]++;
        }
        int champion = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (degree[i] == 0) {
                if (champion == -1) {
                    champion = i;
                } else {
                    return -1;
                }
            }
        }
        return champion;
    }
}
```
This code creates an array `degree` of size `n` to store the number of teams each team is stronger than. It then loops through the `edges` array and for each edge, it increments the degree of the team that is stronger. After that, it loops through the `degree` array and if a team's degree is 0, it checks if a champion has already been found. If not, it sets the champion to be this team. If a champion has already been found, it returns -1 because there is more than one team with degree 0, which means there is no unique champion. Finally, it returns the champion.

